        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You can't remember why you joined the police force, it certainly wasn't to protect and serve. You weren't even out of the academy before you became dirty. You worked the narcotics beat, extracting money, drugs or sexual favors in exchange for not arresting those whom you knew were guilty. For some reason, your sire liked this in you, your raw brutality. As for you, you saw the gift of Malkavian blood as the last thing you needed to realize your full potential. You became a true apex predator, carefully stalking and killing your prey. Unlife became a blur of hunting and destroying other vampires, relishing in their demise. You targeted mostly Anarchs and Thin Bloods, as no one cared enough to protect those. The Brujah, of course, figured tou out and you've learned to step carefully around them. Then, one night, after destroying another Kindred prey, you passed out, only to awaken the next night in the library of the vampire you had killed. He had an extensive library, some books which touched on a thing called Golconda. You'd never heard of this before, but something in the words spoke to you. You had a chance to become more, to overcome your curse. You felt like yourself again. However, Golconda cannot be learned from books, it must be understood through experience. And so you have come to Los Angeles, willing to inject yourself into the politics of the city and test yourself. In addition, you seek out other pupils, those who also walk the path of Golconda, with the idea that by teaching them, you might gain better understanding yourself."
        ],
        [
